Four men were arrested for firing guns at a funeral in Harding, KwaZulu-Natal, at the weekend. Provincial police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said a multi-disciplinary operation was held on Sunday in Harding to monitor a funeral at the Santombe area. Mbele said police heard gunshots being fired in the venue where the funeral was held. She said police swiftly identified the suspects and placed them under arrest. The four men were charged for unlawful possession of firearms and ammunition as well as discharging of a firearm in a public space. Mbele said all the arrested suspects are from the Eastern Cape and were attending a funeral of a man who was shot and killed in Umtata. Three pistols that were found in their possession were seized by the police officers. All four men will appear in the Harding Magistrates Court on Tuesday.